Distribution and habitat: Only known from the type locality (
Fig. 2
), where it lives in an area with Canarian succulent scrub vegetation of the “cardonal” and “tabaibal amargo” type .

Genetic analysis. A fragment of 661 bp was obtained for COI , with an average nucleotide composition for the coding strand of 23.8 % A, 43.2 % T, 14 % C and 18.9 % G. Of a total of 661 bp, 429 ( 64.9 %) were conserved sites, 59 ( 8.9 %) singletons within the data set, and 173 ( 26.2 %) parsimony informative sites. The COI fragments are relatively A-T-rich, as has been observed in other helicid taxa (
Elejalde et al . 2005
).
